		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Heather Sellers</span></strong> is the author of <em>You Don&rsquo;t Look like Anyone I Know</em>, a memoir about family and face blindness. She&rsquo;s also published three books on writing, two volumes of poetry, and one collection of short stories. She teaches at the University of South Florida in Tampa and always composes her first drafts in longhand.</p><a href="/contributors/heather-sellers" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
